{
  "text": "The dual endothelin-1 receptor antagonist bosentan is licenced for the prevention of digital ulcers in patients with SSc and recurrent digital ulcers. Two randomised, double-blind placebo-controlled clinical trials [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] both showed that bosentan reduced the number of new ulcers in patients with SSc and that this effect is most marked in those with multiple ulcers. The more recent RAPIDS-2 study [CITATION_3] included 188 patients who had at least one digital ulcer at baseline: the treatment period was 24 weeks. A number of observational studies have also been published including a recent one from France [CITATION_4] which highlighted how patients who smoke tend to have the most severe digital ulcer disease. In the RAPIDS-2 study [CITATION_5] , the number of new digital ulcers was not reduced in current smokers.Studies of other endothelin receptor antagonists (ERA) are limited. A recent trial of macitentan was discontinued, and data is not yet available.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "6046085",
